        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Kriista</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>about soloing in SF, you can start at 51, dont try before, youll get raped everytime,<BR>where to pull to, towrads BW zoneline, thats the most common 'pull spot'<BR>make a pet, a good one(if 53, rog pet)<BR>/pet taunt off, VERY critical<BR>spells to use, dooming, splurt, ebolt, BoD, and any lifetap available to you, and of course fear<BR>pull with dooming, while running to your pet, ebolt(this is important), then splurt, at this point you should be at your pet, send him in, run towards BW a bit , sitting if neccesary to hold aggro, fear<BR>as SOON as ebolt wears off, reaply dooming<BR>do NOT reply fear however, let it wear off, and let hte mob come back to you, refear if neccessary(dont fear him to far out, and kinda follow it, so it doesnt aggro your pet)<BR>ive found with a max rog pet, hasted, its kind of hard to get aggro off him, even wiht taunt off, and stuff like ebolt in him<BR>all non named will die in 2 doomings, and 2-3fears, <BR>named may need a 3rd dooming, if you pull a named, i reccomend reaplying ebolt after oyur 2nd dooming as its a great timer, <BR>once ebolt goes off, you have about 3chances to get dooming off<BR>it takes a bit to get the feel of when to lich etc..., since the high mana usage, you cant stay in perma lich, so find your niche with it<BR>what to pull:<BR>wurms(bigest wusses there)<BR>sperms, wyverns etc..., i stay away from chromas since hte proc a dispell type thing(though i hvae jboots) it sucks having to reply skin if you lost it, and the way the fly makes it hard to tell how close they are<BR>once you get good wih that, pull named, mature stuff etc....  ,if you overpull, some of hte mobs there hvae that 'lazy' kunark aggro, so if oyu run far and fast, theyll forget about you(mostly the wurms)</P><P>if your with a druid, theres a 'named cycle' of rares<BR>some are:<BR>guardian of felia,wandering wurm, wurm spirit, felia goldensomething, souldevourer, lavawalker, etc...<BR>they give great xp, drop spells often, and are fun to pull<BR>kill one, and in about 1-2min the next one spawns<BR>there is eldrig the old, do not mess with him solo, he summons, and from my experience with him, fear acts funny wiht him<BR>druid i was with pulled him(while i was zoning in), by the time i got with him he was almost dead(the durid), i figured, np, we keep him feared and he wont summon<BR>i feared him, then this part happened fast, but i swear that he summoned/killed the druid, adn then was running towrads me<BR>now i know the fear pathing pretty well there, and it looked like the  fucker was heading at me, fear wore off, he proced some DOT on me, i FDed and /q out<BR>leason learned</P><P>its all and all, fun, challenging, nearly always empty, great xp, good spell drops<BR>its ALOT more work than CS type mobs, so keep that in mind<BR>NEVER let dooming come off, NEVER fear them too far, go, and youll learn why</P><P></P><P>54necro<BR>35monk<BR>Veeshan</font></td>
