        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Abaraxas</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>There's a good little spot to the right of the OT zone (coming from OT). Head to the far end of the little plateau, park your pet and pull anything and everything with dooming, chromadracs give you the shits but there's so many of them you might as well risk a little debuffing, throw in a Splurt as you run back to your pet. Quickly swap dooming for cascading dark, sic pet and fear, hit em with cascading and maybe throw in EB or COC for laughs. BOD when you need to.</P><P>The pathing here should keep them on the plateau heading towards the OT zone at which point they will turn and head down to the valley below. With taunt off, you can get them to go after you when fear breaks which is good for the 53 pet to keep on backstabbing. The only safety spell I use here is PE for when the first dark doesn't stick. Can give you time to recast dark or run for the zone if you need to. Never seen any spell over lvl 53 drop in this spot but when BW zone gets too crowded it's a nice add-free XP spot.</P><P>Abaraxas Malfoy<BR>Defiler of the Tribunal</font></td>
